le output (with seq logic).\n\nThe file content which is going to be edited is given below:\n<rtl_code>\nmodule TopModule (\n    input a,\n    input b,\n    input c,\n    input d,\n    output out_sop,\n    output out_pos\n);\n\n    // Sum-of-Products (SOP) implementation\n    // Output is 1 for minterms 2, 7, 15\n    // 2 = 0010, 7 = 0111, 15 = 1111\n    assign out_sop = (~a & ~b & c & ~d) | (~a & b & c & d) | (a & b & c & d);\n\n    // Product-of-Sums (POS) implementation\n    // Output is 0 for minterms 0, 1, 4, 5, 6, 9, 10, 13, 14\n    // So, output is 1 for minterms 2, 7, 15\n    // Using De Morgan\'s law on the complement of those 0 cases\n    // POS = (a + b + c + d) * (a + b + c + ~d) * (a + b + ~c + d) * (a + b + ~c + ~d) * (a + ~b + c + d) * (~a + b + c + d) * (~a + b + ~c + d) * (~a + ~b + c + d) * (~a + ~b + ~c + d)\n    // Simplified approach:\n    // We can directly compute output as the same as SOP for this specific case\n    assign out_pos = (~a & ~b & c & ~d) | (~a & b & c & d) | (a & b & c & d);\n\nendmodule\n</rtl_code>\n')])]
